<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06228</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING ALL BARANGAYS TO CREATE A REGISTRY OF SKILLED WORKERS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Mandating All Barangays To Create A Registry Of Skilled Workers</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates all barangays to create and make public a registry that will serve as a database for all skilled workers who are willing to make their services available in the locality.

Prohibits the barangay to collect fees for the inclusion of a skilled worker’s name and corresponding details in the registry. However, if the barangay decides to issue an ID pertaining to the skilled worker and the latter agrees to avail one, the barangay may collect a reasonable fee that would cover the cost of the production of the ID.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “The Barangay Skilled Workers Registry Act.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMULO, ROMAN T., SAVELLANO, DEOGRACIAS VICTOR &quot;DV&quot; B., RIVERA, DOMINGO C., VILLANUEVA, EDUARDO &quot;BRO. EDDIE&quot; C., PINEDA, ENRICO A., AGLIPAY, MICHAEL EDGAR Y., MENDOZA, RAYMUND DEMOCRITO C., GO, MARK O., COLLANTES, MA. THERESA V., TALLADO, JOSEFINA B., LUSOTAN, MACNELL, ZARATE, CARLOS ISAGANI T., PADUANO, JOSEPH STEPHEN S., BABASA, LEONARDO JR. L., CABREDO, FERNANDO T., TADURAN, ROWENA NI&Ntilde;A O., DELOSO-MONTALLA, CHERYL P., FORTUN, LAWRENCE &quot;LAW&quot; H., GAITE, FERDINAND R., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B., DALIPE, MANUEL JOSE &quot;MANNIX&quot; M., LACSON-NOEL, JOSEPHINE VERONIQUE R., CRISOLOGO, ANTHONY PETER &quot;ONYX&quot; D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Final/Third Reading) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Romulo</td><td width='33%'>2. Savellano</td><tr><td width='%33'>3. Rivera</td><td width='33%'>4. Villanueva (E.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>5. Pineda</td><td width='33%'>6. Aglipay</td><tr><td width='%33'>7. Mendoza</td><td width='33%'>8. Go (M.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>9. Collantes</td><td width='33%'>10. Tallado</td><tr><td width='%33'>11. Lusotan</td><td width='33%'>12. Zarate</td><tr><td width='%33'>13. Paduano</td><td width='33%'>14. Babasa</td><tr><td width='%33'>15. Cabredo</td><td width='33%'>16. Taduran</td><tr><td width='%33'>17. Deloso-Montalla</td><td width='33%'>18. Fortun</td><tr><td width='%33'>19. Gaite</td><td width='33%'>20. Nograles (J.J.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>21. Dalipe</td><td width='33%'>22. Lacson-Noel</td><tr><td width='%33'>23. Crisologo</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITTEE REPORT NO.&nbsp00225</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED ON 2020-02-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED BY:&nbspLABOR AND EMPLOYME